# FRONTEND RULES — Grain v6

Mobile-first PWA.

Minimal. Calm. Intentional.

---

## Design Tokens

All styles reference CSS custom properties from `grain-tokens.css`.
Never hardcode colors, spacing, or font values.

### Colors (Authoritative)

Source of truth: **Grain — Final Color System (03/03/2026)**

Base tokens:
- Background: `--bg`, `--bg-card`, `--bg-input`, `--bg-elevated`
- Border: `--border`, `--border-subtle`
- Accent (Meridian): `--accent`, `--accent-soft`, `--accent-glow`
- Text: `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-muted`
- Status: `--status-aligned`, `--status-aligned-soft`, `--status-drift`, `--status-drift-soft`, `--status-misaligned`, `--status-misaligned-soft`

Extended accents (semantic-only):
- Blue (activity/data): `--accent-blue`, `--accent-blue-soft`, `--accent-blue-glow`, `--accent-blue-text`, `--accent-blue-emphasis`
- Amber (milestones/urgency): `--accent-amber`, `--accent-amber-soft`, `--accent-amber-glow`, `--accent-amber-text`, `--accent-amber-emphasis`
- Violet (categories/insights): `--accent-violet`, `--accent-violet-soft`, `--accent-violet-glow`, `--accent-violet-text`, `--accent-violet-emphasis`

Shadows:
- `--shadow-card`, `--shadow-elevated`, `--shadow-glow` (dark), `--shadow-input-focus` (light)

### Color Usage Rules (Enforced)

**Accent (`--accent`)**
Use ONLY for elements the user should interact with or data the user should notice.
- Use for: primary buttons, selected chips/toggles, selected hour blocks, progress arc, key metrics, active input borders, links
- Do not use for: decorative backgrounds, non-interactive icons, body text, card backgrounds (use `--accent-soft`), status indicators

**Status colors**
Status colors appear only in data contexts (Home trajectory cards, Review, Journey). Never decorative.
- Never on buttons
- Never used as general text color (only inside badges/data labels)
- Never used in onboarding
- Use soft variants as badge/tag backgrounds

**Extended accents**
Blue/Amber/Violet are semantic-only. Never interchangeable with `--accent`.
- Never for primary interactive elements (use `--accent`)
- Never for status indicators
- Never for decoration

**Text hierarchy (3 levels only)**
- `--text-primary`: headlines, body text, key data
- `--text-secondary`: supporting descriptions, secondary data
- `--text-muted`: labels, timestamps, placeholders, metadata

No fourth text level.

### Typography
- Logo: DM Serif Text 400
- All UI: DM Sans
- Screen headline: 22px/28.6px Bold
- Welcome headline: 26px/33.8px Bold
- Card title: 15px/24px SemiBold (600)
- Body/subhead: 13px/19.5px Regular
- Button: 13px/19.5px Medium (500)
- Chip: 13px/19.5px Regular
- Section label: 10px SemiBold (600) uppercase, letter-spacing 0.12px
- Caption: 11px/16.5px Regular
- Hour display: 64px/64px Bold
- Commitment value: 16px/16px Bold

### Spacing
- Content padding: 24px horizontal
- Headline top: 32px padding-top
- Headline bottom: 8px padding-bottom
- Subhead to content: 20px
- Between cards: 8px
- CTA zone: 28px padding-top, 56px padding-bottom, 12px gap between buttons

### Radius
- Buttons/inputs/cards: 14px
- Chips: 22px
- Hour blocks: 8px
- Progress dots: 2px
- Drawer top corners: 22px
- Full circle: 999px

